						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="event" href="/en/Dossiers/S-T-Issues/Climate-change/Related-developments/Conference-Hunger-Climate-Change" title="Conference: Hunger &amp; Climate Change" alt="event">Conference: Hunger &amp; Climate Change</a></h2>

	
	
					<p>Almost one billion people in the world are hungry today. And the world’s population will continue to grow until it stabilises at nine billion in the middle of this century, by which time our food systems will have to feed 50% more people than they do today. Achieving this would be a challenge anyway. The likely impact of climate change on agriculture will make the challenge even greater.</p>
					<p><span class="date">Tuesday 03 March 2009 - Tuesday 03 March 2009</p><div class="cnt">
	<a class="event" href="/en/Dossiers/S-T-Issues/Climate-change/Related-developments/Conference-Hunger-Climate-Change">Read more...</a>
