					<p>The problem of global warming from greenhouse gases calls for a stronger involvement of agriculture and farming communities, as well as forestry and forest users in reducing greenhouse gas emissions, FAO said today. &quot;Agriculture and deforestation are major contributors to climate change, but by the same token farmers and forest users could become key players in reducing greenhouse gas emissions,&quot; said Alexander Müller, FAO Assistant Director-General. (Source: FAO, 4 December 2008).</p>
